tp:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Prize_in_Physics\" title=\"Nobel Prize in Physics\">Nobel Prize in Physics<\/a>, and the 2015 <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Breakthrough_Prize_in_Fundamental_Physics\" title=\"Breakthrough Prize in Fundamental Physics\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Breakthrough Prize in Fundamental Physics<\/a> with <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Brian_P._Schmidt\" title=\"Brian P. Schmidt\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Brian P. Schmidt<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Adam_Riess\" title=\"Adam Riess\">Adam Riess<\/a> for providing evidence that the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Accelerating_universe\" title=\"Accelerating universe\">expansion of the universe is accelerating<\/a>.<\/p>","name":"Saul Perlmutter","place_of_birth":"Champaign-Urbana ,  Illinois ,  U.S.","place_of_death":null,"text":"Saul Perlmutter , Physics, 2011","year":2011.0}